name: microservices-notification-service
description: This repository contains the source code for a Notification Service built using Java Spring Boot.This application utilise apache kafka to accept notifications and print it on console for confirmation.

description: Microservice Library application with Spring Boot

description: Technologies used: Azure DevOps, Terraform, Docker, Spring Boot

description: Grpc microservice server in go for Slowfood food-order service application.

name: Carties
description: This is Microservices application for Carties

name: microservices-with-openfeign
description: This is a two-microservice application: one for Employee Service and another for Department Service. They communicate with each other using OpenFeign Client. The tools and technologies used in this application include Java 8, Spring Boot REST API, Microservices architecture, MySQL, Spring Actuator, and OpenFeign Client.

name: microservices-with-webclient
description: This is a two-microservice application: one for Employee Microservices and another for Department Microservices. We facilitate communication between both microservices using WebClient. The tools and technologies used include Java 8, Spring Boot, MySQL, Microservices architecture, Spring Actuator, and WebClient.

name: dadjoke-provider-a-kubernetes-microservices-project
description: In this project, we've built a Dad Joke Provider application using a microservices architecture and deployed it on a Kubernetes cluster. This project serves as an excellent introduction to containerization, microservices, and Kubernetes orchestration.

name: Banking-Service
description: This is the banking service application builded based on the microservice architecture

name: DemoServer
description: This project is a Spring Boot application that exposes several web services. It uses an H2 in-memory database to store the input data provided via XML. The web services allow clients to send XML payloads, which are then processed and saved to the H2 database.

name: Movie-Ticket-Booking
description: A microservices-based application that replicates the core functionalities of the BookMyShow platform. The project includes services for managing movies, theaters, and seat bookings, leveraging Spring Boot and Spring Cloud for a scalable and maintainable architecture.

name: api-gateway
description: A Spring Boot application that routes requests to Game Service API and Auth-Service API, acting as a single entry point. It handles JWT authentication, request validation, and load balancing, enhancing efficiency and security in the microservice architecture.

name: accountservice
description: This project demonstrates the integration of Spring Boot with Apache Kafka to implement a scalable and reliable messaging system for asynchronous communication between microservices. The application is designed to produce and consume messages in a Kafka topic to enable seamless event-driven architecture.
